From: Herbert Xu <herbert@gondor.apana.org.au>
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 2026 15:30:20 +0900
Subject: crypto: algif_aead - Revert to operating out-of-place
Patch-mainline: v7.0-rc7
Git-commit: a664bf3d603dc3bdcf9ae47cc21e0daec706d7a5
References: bsc#1262573 CVE-2026-31431

This mostly reverts commit 72548b093ee3 except for the copying of
the associated data.

There is no benefit in operating in-place in algif_aead since the
source and destination come from different mappings.  Get rid of
all the complexity added for in-place operation and just copy the
AD directly.

Fixes: 72548b093ee3 ("crypto: algif_aead - copy AAD from src to dst")
Reported-by: Taeyang Lee <0wn@theori.io>
Signed-off-by: Herbert Xu <herbert@gondor.apana.org.au>
[~nstange: adapt to skipped patches, most notably to
 c1abe6f570af ("crypto: af_alg: Use extract_iter_to_sg() to create
 scatterlists.")]
Acked-by: Nicolai Stange <nstange@suse.de>
